	<string name="help">
		Help for you:\n
		You are in a Rubik Cube learning activity OK?\n\n

		How to use the cube:\n
		- You can see 3 different little cubes up in the screen\n
		- them do not change never and i call this CUBE.\n
		- If u press F R U B L D buttons u do a MOVE Clockwise in the CUBE.\n
		- If u see a letter with \' after (like F\') that mean the move of the CUBE is ANTI-clockwise.\n
		- Center are always at the same GOOD place in the CUBE.\n
		- If u swap on the image u ROTATE the cube without modifying the CUBE, i call this SWAP-CUBE.\n
		- the SWAP-CUBE is drawn in the BIG image.\n
		That mean that if u have to ROTATE the cube then do an algorithm read in pdf\n
		u should see WHERE the F R U B L D face is right now in the SWAP-CUBE,\n
		then do the MOVE according to the COLOUR of the BUTTON,\n
		that ALWAYS indicates the center of the face.\n\n

		Auxiliary buttons:\n
		in menu there are 4 buttons:\n
		- Random: it do 10 random moves\n
		- Reset: it colour the cube back to the "clear" one.\n
		- Save: it let u save the last cube u used for long term uses\n
		    (do it before u clean the activity if u wish to restart from this cube).\n
		- Load: it let u re-load the last cube u saved.\n\n
		<!--You can also CHANGE CUBE COLORS if u prefer it, to adapt them to a real-life cube,
		or for personalize it in FUNNY ways…, but it may add difficulties to learning solving it.\n-->

		How to learn:\n
		in menu there are three buttons "visualize PDF", "import PDF" and "write your algorithm",\n
		have fun trying them :3\n

		have fun learning and playing!
	</string>


